te</i>, Danish <i>Holtsete</i> ‘person from Holstein’.","Dutch (also <b>Van Holst</b>): habitational name for someone from any of several places so called, from <i>holst, hulst</i> ‘holly (forest)’. Compare   Hulst  ."]},{"name":"Holsten","meanings":["North German: variant of   Holstein   or   Holst  ."]}]},{"name":"Adolf","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>Adelwolf</i>, a compound of <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>wolf</i> ‘wolf’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Count","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>counte</i> ‘count’ (Old French <i>conte</i>, from Latin <i>comes</i>, <i>comitem</i>); a title of French and Norman nobility, ranking as equivalent to English   Earl  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Earl","meanings":["North American: from the title originally adopted as a nickname parallel to   Duke  ,   King  , etc. The title was used in England in Norman times as an equivalent of the French <i>comte</i> ‘count’ it is from Old English <i>eorl</i> ‘warrior, nobleman, prince’. In some cases the given name may have been taken from the surname <i>Earl</i>, which was originally either a nickname or a term denoting someone who worked in the household of an earl."]}]},{"name":"Of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adolf V Count Of Holstein was born in 1252. He married Euphemia Alenta Samborowna von ost pommern about 1280. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1308, in Germany, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1252–1308":"1252–1308","1250–1309":"1250–1309","1281–1318":"1281–1318","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","Abt 1281":"umbes 1281","1309":"1309","1308":"1308","1281":"